Doesnt change much because slope and seasons were already significant; we are just re-assigning the 0.0118 variation from interaction back to the other model terms.

P=0.79, so the two models do not have statistically different explanatory power. Likely because there really wasnt much difference in fit lines of the same slopes model vs.the separate slopes model.
